2.00	%C4%8CSD_Class_387.0	ČSD Class 387.0	The ČSD Class 387.0 were 4-6-2 express passenger steam locomotives operated by the Czechoslovak State Railways (Československé státní dráhy, ČSD) between 1926 and 1974. Forty-three of these 2,100-horsepower (1,570 kW) pacific locomotives were built by the Škoda Works, Plzeň in five series between 1926 and 1937, intended for the heaviest long-distance express trains.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d0/387_Luschna_%28cropped%29.jpg/300px-387_Luschna_%28cropped%29.jpg
